ann:label: Flu with symptomatic and asymptomatic infections as well as outcomes from infection
ann:description: Classic SEIR model extended to include both symptomatic and an asymptomatic infectious states as well as hospitalization, ventilation, death, as well as, vaccinated.

userInput.ann:label: Sucsceptibility Factor
userInput.ann:description: Level of susceptibility of an uninfected individual.

userInput.ann:label: Infectious and symptomatic
userInput.ann:description: Infectious with symptoms. Symptomatic individuals are more likely to be observed, thus counted or eligible for interventions.

userInput.ann:label: Infectious but asympotmatic
userInput.ann:description: Infectious without symptoms. Asymptomatic individuals are less likely to infect others or be observed, thus may not be counted and are less likely to receive interventions.

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Asymptomatic Progression
userInput.ann:description: Proportion of Infectious that are asymptomatic.  Represents the probability an individual in the Exposed state will become Infectious and asymtomatic.

exceads.name: Influenza Disease Model with vaccination and outcomes
